Kapitel 1

Zu merken:

Kernel = Controller for the Applications. The kernel also abstracts the complicated details away from the application. The Kernel is the communication connection between the Hardware and Applications. The Applications sends requests to the kernel to start process.

process = is just one task that is loaded and tracked by the kernel.

Linux started out in 1991 as a hobby project by Linus Torvalds.

Source code is not understood directly by the computer, so it must be compiled into machine instructions by a compiler.

UNIX is owned by Open Group. Software certified by the Open Group is called UNIX.

Linux really isn’t UNIX, it is not certified! It’s just… UNIX-like.

Open source is that yiu have the right to obtain the software and to modify it for own use.

Distributors:	Red Hat, Scientific Linux, Open SUSE, Debian, Ubuntu, Linux Mint

A command is a software program that when executed on the command line, performs an action on the computer

Aliases = An alias can override a built-in command
Functions = Functions can also be built using existing commands to either create new commands